    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling performance today, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (83.19), who represents our premier play. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable matchup against Lorenzen, making him the centerpiece of our offensive strategy. Close behind him are **Jacob Wilson** (67.19) and **Miguel Vargas** (66.33), both of whom capitalize on high park-factor environments. Specifically, **Miguel Vargas** earns his high score through a unique intersection of factors: the 10% park boost and the rare \"Slow SP Delivery\" edge against Springs, which enhances his stolen base potential\u2014a critical factor given our prioritization of speed in this 5x5 format.\n\nThe most difficult decision today was excluding **Nolan Schanuel** (55.84) from the starting nine. While **Nolan Schanuel** projected as a solid asset against King, he ultimately fell short of the threshold required to displace players like **Josh Lowe** (60.13), whose dynamic platoon advantage provided the necessary edge to justify his start. We are closely monitoring the risk inherent in **Jackson Merrill** (53.94); while his base metrics are steady, he faces a daunting challenge against a pitcher in Urena who, despite the 2.35 xERA, may be prone to regression\u2014though we must treat that xERA as an elite-arm warning that caps his ceiling. \n\nAcross the rest of the diamond, we are looking for significant contributions from **Andy Pages** (68.47) and **Marcell Ozuna** (65.09). **Andy Pages** benefits from the same park conditions as **Kyle Tucker**, while **Marcell Ozuna** receives a critical wind-out boost to pair with his favorable matchup against McClanahan. Although **Gunnar Henderson** (54.20) and **Drake Baldwin** (54.09) sit firmly in the marginal range due to specific platoon disadvantages, their position in the top half of the order keeps them in the lineup. Conversely, **Liam Hicks** (42.70) remains our most vulnerable starter; his score is buoyed almost entirely by a platoon edge, and any change in the defensive alignment behind the plate could shift his daily utility.",
